dcterms:description: The Flow-RBC dataset comprises 98,240 training examples and 23,104 test examples. Each input set represents the distribution of 1,000 red blood cells (RBCs). Each RBC is characterized by volume and hemoglobin content measurements. The task involves regression, aiming to predict the corresponding hematocrit level measured on the same blood sample.
dcterms:title: Flow-RBC

dcterms:description: The Celebrity Together dataset consists of images depicting multiple celebrities together, making it a suitable choice for evaluating set retrieval methods. Unlike other face datasets that only include individual face crops, Celebrity Together comprises full images with multiple labeled faces.
dcterms:title: Celebrity Together

dcterms:description: SHIFT15M is a dataset designed specifically for assessing models in set-to-set matching scenarios, considering distribution shift assumptions. It allows for evaluating model performance across different levels of dataset shifts by adjusting the magnitude.
dcterms:title: SHIFT15M

dcterms:description: ShapeNet is a large scale repository for 3D CAD models. The repository contains over 300M models with 220,000 classified into 3,135 classes arranged using WordNet hypernym-hyponym relationships.

dcterms:description: 3D MNIST is a 3D version of the MNIST database of handwritten digits. This dataset contains 3D point clouds generated from the original images of the MNIST dataset, and it contains 6,000 instances.
